              "body": "The highest-leverage customization pattern in production. Use a strong, expensive **teacher** model to generate ideal outputs or labels for your task, then **fine-tune a small, cheap student** model on those examples.\n\nThe student can't match the teacher at *everything* — but on *your one narrow task* it gets remarkably close, at a fraction of the per-call cost and latency. This is how you get near-frontier quality at small-model prices: let the big model do the hard thinking once (to create the dataset), then bottle that behavior into a model small enough to serve cheaply at scale. It pairs naturally with model routing (m2l4): the distilled student handles the routine 80%, the frontier model handles the hard 20%."
