              "id": "m4l6-i5",
              "front": "When using LLM-as-judge for RAG evaluation, what precautions keep the scores trustworthy?",
              "back": "Validate judge scores against human ratings, use a strong *separate* judge model (not the same model that generated the output, to avoid shared blind spots), and watch for known biases toward longer/more confident answers and position bias."
