              "front": "Distinguish a chain, a workflow, and an agent by who controls the path.",
              "back": "A chain is a fixed developer-hardcoded sequence of LLM calls. A workflow is a graph with conditional edges where the developer defines every possible path and the LLM picks the branch. An agent has no fixed graph — the model decides each step and when it's done."
