              "id": "m5l3-i1",
              "front": "Name the three conditions that genuinely justify a multi-agent system over a single well-designed agent.",
              "back": "(1) Specialization pays — subtasks need distinct tools/prompts/models; (2) parallelism helps — independent subtasks cut wall-clock time; (3) independent verification matters — a separate agent checks the generator without bias. If none apply, use one agent."
