              "type": "text",
              "heading": "Why Agents Need Memory",
              "body": "LLMs are stateless — each API call starts from scratch. But useful agents need to remember: what happened earlier in the conversation, what the user prefers, what entities have been mentioned, and what tasks are in progress.\n\nMemory is what turns a stateless tool-caller into a coherent agent. The right memory architecture depends on your use case."
