              "front": "Contrast SHAP/feature attribution with an LLM-generated explanation, and what's the robust pattern?",
              "back": "SHAP is faithful to the model — it attributes the prediction to actual input features. An LLM narration is a readable but post-hoc story that may not reflect the real reasoning. The robust pattern: compute real drivers with SHAP, then have the LLM narrate those specific attributions."
