              "id": "m7l5-i1",
              "front": "Why do AI system costs surprise teams in ways traditional software costs don't?",
              "back": "Traditional cost scales with compute (predictable); AI cost scales with tokens (variable and user-dependent). A single verbose or adversarial user, a retry-triggering prompt, or a runaway agent loop can 10x spend in hours or minutes."
